Key Match Events: Golden State led by 31 points in the first half
Houston tied the game with an 18-2 run in the fourth quarter
Golden State scored the first six points in overtime
Jabari Smith Jr. tied the game with a 3-pointer
Aaron Holiday stole the ball and fouled out Draymond Green
Tari Eason made two free throws to send it to overtime
Jonathan Kuminga scored the first two baskets of overtime
Houston made just 1 of 12 shots in overtime
Post-Match Reflections: Golden State continued to win without Steph Curry, improving to 5-1 this season
Andrew Wiggins added 15 points for Golden State in his return after missing two games
Miscellaneous Highlights: It’s Golden State’s 14th straight-regular season win over the Rockets and the eighth in a row in Houston
Warriors led by five before a 3-pointer by Jabari Smith Jr. cut the lead to 119-117
Eason led the Rockets with a career-high 27 points
